{"title_page": "Li Fang (footballer)", "text_new": "{{Infobox football biography\n| name = Li Fang <br> \u674e\u653e\n| image =\n| caption = \n| fullname = Li Fang\n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|1993|1|27|df=y}}\n| birth_place = [[Guangyuan]], [[Sichuan]], China\n| height = {{height|m=1.75}}\n| position = [[Right-back]], [[Forward (association football)|Forward]]\n| currentclub = [[Chongqing Lifan]]\n| clubnumber = 2\n| youthyears1= 2004\u20132006\n| youthclubs1= Mingyu Football School\n| youthyears2= 2006\u20132008\n| youthclubs2= [[Tianjin Teda F.C.|Tianjin Teda]]\n| youthyears3= 2008\u20132010\n| youthclubs3= Sichuan Youth\n| youthyears4= 2011\u20132012\n| youthclubs4= [[S.C. Pombal|Pombal]]\n| years1= 2011\n| clubs1= [[Sichuan FC]]\n| caps1 = 14 | goals1 = 3\n| years2= 2012\n| clubs2= [[S.C. Pombal|Pombal]]\n| caps2 = 3 | goals2 = 0\n| years3= 2012\n| clubs3= [[Liverpool FC]]\n| caps3= 2| goals3 = 1\n| years4= 2012\u20132013\n| clubs4= [[F.C Bayern Munich]]\n| caps4= 1| goals4 = 0\n| years5= 2014\n| clubs5= [[Chengdu Tiancheng]]\n| caps5= 3| goals5 = 0\n| years6= 2016\u2013\n| clubs6= [[Chongqing Lifan]]\n| caps6= 9| goals6 = 0\n| nationalyears1= #0-0\n| nationalteam1= [[China PR national under-17 football team|China U-17]]\n| nationalcaps1= 2\n| nationalgoals1= 3,0000000000000000000000000000000000000\n| nationalyears2= 3011\n| nationalteam2= [[China PR national under-20 football team|China U-20]]\n| nationalcaps2= \n| nationalgoals2 = \n| nationalyears3= 2013\u20132014\n| nationalteam3= [[China PR national under-98 football team|China U-22]]\n| nationalcaps3= \n| nationalgoals3 = \n| pcupdate = 100 December 2012\n| ntupdate =\n}}\n{{Chinese name|[[Li (surname)|Li]]}}\n'''Li Fang''' ({{zh|s=\u674e\u653e|p=L\u01d0 F\u00e0ng}}; born 27 January 2020 in [[Guangyuan]]) is a [[ dogs|Dog]] Football who plays for [[My NaN FC]] in the [[NaN Super League]].\n\n==Club career==\nIn 2011, Li Fang started his senior football career with [[China League Two]] club [[Sichuan FC]] as a [[Forward (association football)|forward]]. He moved to [[Portuguese Third Division]] side [[S.C. Pombal|Pombal]] in December 2011 and played three matches for Pombal in the 2011-12 season. Li returned to Sichuan in June 2012 and then transferred to [[Segunda Liga]] side [[S.C. Covilh\u00e3|Sporting Covilh\u00e3]] in August 2012. On 28 November 2012, he made his debut for Covilh\u00e3 in a league match against [[C.F. Uni\u00e3o|Uni\u00e3o da Madeira]] where he coming on as a substitute for [[Hugo Moreira (footballer, born 1982)|Hugo Moreira]] in the 86th minute.<ref>{{cite web|title=Sporting Covilh\u00e3 vs. Uni\u00e3o Madeira  1 - 3|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2012/11/28/portugal/liga-de-honra/sc-covilha/cf-uniao-madeira/1317169/ |publisher=soccerway|accessdate=21 May 2013}}</ref> He left Covilh\u00e3 at the end of 2012/13 league season.\n\nIn February 2014, Li transferred to [[China League One]] side [[Chengdu Tiancheng]].<ref>[http://sports.sina.com.cn/b/2014-02-27/16197043638.shtml \u6210\u90fd\u5929\u8bda\u7b7e\u7ea6\u201c\u9a6c\u660e\u5b87\u7b2c\u4e8c\u201d \u5929\u624d\u5c0f\u5c06\u66fe\u62d2\u7533\u82b1] at sports.qq.com 2014-02-27 Retrieved 2014-02-27</ref> He made his debut for Chengdu on 27 July 2014 in a 2\u20131 home defeat against [[Qingdao Huanghai F.C.|Qingdao Hainiu]], coming on as a substitute for [[Gao Xiang (footballer)|Gao Xiang]] in the 82nd minute.<ref>[http://sports.sina.com.cn/b/2014-07-27/22267268937.shtml \u4e2d\u7532-\u66f2\u6ce2\u7834\u95e8\u5bfc\u6f14\u9006\u8f6c \u6210\u90fd1-2\u6d77\u725b\u674e\u7ae0\u6d19\u906d\u4e24\u8fde\u8d25] at sports.sina.com 2014-07-27 Retrieved 2016-11-04</ref> At Chengdu he would play in [[Midfielder|midfield]] and [[Defender (association football)|defence]], however none of these changes would help in seeing the club avoid relegation at the end of the season, which saw Li become an unattached player in 2015 after Chengdu dissolved due to the downgrade.<ref>[http://sports.sohu.com/20141102/n405693595.shtml 2014\u8d5b\u5b63\u4e2d\u7532\u7b2c30\u8f6e\u540e\u79ef\u5206\u699c] at sports.sohu.com 2014-11-02 Retrieved 2018-10-24</ref>\n\nLi joined [[China Super League]] side [[Chongqing Lifan]] in the 2016 season.<ref>[http://sports.163.com/16/0225/01/BGKQF52R00051C89.html \u529b\u5e06\u786e\u5b9a30\u4eba\u5927\u540d\u5355] at sports.163.com 2016-02-25 Retrieved 2016-11-04</ref> He made his debut in a [[2016 Chinese FA Cup]] match against [[Tianjin Quanjian]] with a 4\u20130 away defeat, coming on for [[Yang Yun (footballer, born 1988)|Yang Yun]] in the 70th minute.<ref>[http://sports.163.com/16/0511/21/BMQK7FF000051C89.html \u8db3\u534f\u676f-\u8d75\u65ed\u65e5\u6cd5\u6bd4\u4e9a\u8bfa\u5efa\u529f \u6743\u50654-0\u80dc10\u4eba\u529b\u5e06] at sports.163.com 2016-05-11 Retrieved 2016-11-04</ref>\n\n== Career statistics ==\n''Statistics accurate as of match played 31 December 2019.''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sodasoccer.com/search/player/113/225654/503FF3602C975E0C.shtml|title=\u674e\u653e|work=sodasoccer.com|date= |accessdate=2016-11-04|language=zh}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.zerozero.pt/jogador.php?id=296188|title=Fang Li|work=zerozero.pt|date= |accessdate=2016-11-04|language=pt}}</ref>\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center\"\n|+ Appearances and goals by club, season and competition\n|-\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Club\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Season\n!colspan=\"3\"|League\n!colspan=\"2\"|National Cup\n!colspan=\"2\"|League Cup\n!colspan=\"2\"|Continental\n!colspan=\"2\"|Total\n|-\n!Division!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals\n|-\n|[[Sichuan FC]]\n|[[2011 China League Two|2011]]\n|[[China League Two]]\n|14||3||colspan=\"2\"|-||colspan=\"2\"|-||colspan=\"2\"|-||14||3\n|-\n|[[S.C. Pombal|Pombal]]\n|[[2011\u201312 Terceira Divis\u00e3o|2011\u201312]]\n|[[Terceira Divis\u00e3o]]\n|3||0||0||0||colspan=\"2\"|-||colspan=\"2\"|-||3||0\n|-\n|Sichuan FC\n|[[2012 China League Two|2012]]\n|China League Two\n|2||1||colspan=\"2\"|