uro of the Communist Party of China|18th]], [[19th Politburo of the Communist Party of China|19th]] Politburo Standing Committee\n| 2007\u2013: [[17th Politburo of the Communist Party of China|17th]], [[18th Politburo of the Communist Party of China|18th]], [[19th Politburo of the Communist Party of China|19th]] Politburo\n| 2007\u20132012: Secretary (first-ranked), 17th Central Secretariat\n| 2002\u2013: Full member, [[16th Central Committee of the Communist Party of China|16th]], [[17th Central Committee of the Communist Party of China|17th]], [[18th Central Committee of the Communist Party of China|18th]], [[19th Central Committee of the Communist Party of China|19th]] Central Committee\n| 1997\u20132002: Alternate member, [[15th Central Committee of the Communist Party of China|15th]] Central Committee\n| 1998\u2013: Delegate, 9th, 10th, 11th, 12th National People's Congress\n}}\n----\n{{Collapsible list\n|titlestyle = background-color:#FCF;text-align:center;\n|title = Leading Groups and Commissions\n|bullets = on\n| 2018\u2013present: Leader, [[Leading Group for Financial and Economic Affairs|Central Financial and Economic Affairs Commission]]\n| 2018\u2013present: Chairman, [[Foreign Affairs Leading Small Group of the Communist Party of China|Central Commission on Foreign Affairs]]\n| 2018\u2013present: Chairman, [[Central Leading Group for Internet Security and Informatization|Central Commission on Internet Affairs]]\n| 2018\u2013present: Chairman, [[Central Leading Group for Comprehensively Deepening Reforms|Commission on Comprehensively Deepening Reforms]]\n| 2014\u2013present: Leader, [[Central Leading Group for Military Reform|Leading Group for Defence and Military Reform]]\n| 2014\u20132018: Leader, [[Central Leading Group for Internet Security and Informatization|Leading Group for Internet Security and Informatization]]\n| 2013\u2013present: Chairman, [[National Security Commission of the Communist Party of China|National Security Commission]]\n| 2013\u