17)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://en.kremlin.ru/events/president/news/54973|title=Presenting the Order of St Andrew the Apostle to President of China Xi Jinping|last=|first=|date=4 July 2017|website=The Kremlin|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190811022033/http://en.kremlin.ru/events/president/news/54973|archive-date=11 August 2019|access-date=7 September 2019}}</ref>\n* [[File:Order Zayed rib.png|85x85px]] {{flagu|United Arab Emirates}}: [[Order of Zayed]] (20 July 2018)<ref name=\"UAE Order of Zayed2\">{{cite news|url=https://www.thenational.ae/uae/government/china-visit-uae-leadership-strikes-strategic-deals-with-xi-jinping-1.752319|title=China visit: UAE leadership strikes strategic deals with Xi Jinping|last1=Dennehy|first1=John|date=20 July 2018|work=[[The National (Abu Dhabi)|The National]]|accessdate=22 July 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180722070115/https://www.thenational.ae/uae/government/china-visit-uae-leadership-strikes-strategic-deals-with-xi-jinping-1.752319|archive-date=22 July 2018|url-status=live}}</ref>\n* [[File:ARG Order of the Liberator San Martin - Grand Cross BAR.png|85x85px]] {{flagu|Argentina}}: [[Order of the Liberator General San Martin|Collar of the Order of the Liberator General San Martin]] (2 December 2018)<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://news.cgtn.com/news/3d3d414d3549444d31457a6333566d54/share.html|title=President Xi awarded Argentina's highest decoration|last=|first=|date=3 December 2018|newspaper=[[CGTN]]|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=7 September 2019}}</ref>\n* [[File:KRG Order Manas.png|85x85px]] {{flagu|Kyrgyzstan}}: [[:ru:\u041e\u0440\u0434\u0435\u043d \u00ab\u041c\u0430\u043d\u0430\u0441\u00bb#\u0421\u0441\u044b\u043b\u043a\u0438|Order of Manas]] (13 June 2019)<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.chinadaily.com.cn/global/2019-06/14/content_37480672.htm|title=Xi honored for building Kyrgyz ties|last=An|first=Baijie|last2=Cao|first2=Desheng|date=14 June 2019|newspaper=[[China Daily]]|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=7 September 2019}}</ref>\n* {{flagu|Tajikistan}}: Order of the Crown (15 June 2019)<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://news.ru/world/si-czinpin-nagrazhdyon-vysshim-ordenom-tadzhikistana/|title=|last=|first=|date=15 June 2019|newspaper=[[NEWSru]]|language=ru|script-title=ru:\u0421\u0438 \u0426\u0437\u0438\u043d\u044c\u043f\u0438\u043d \u043d\u0430\u0433\u0440\u0430\u0436\u0434\u0451\u043d \u0432\u044b\u0441\u0448\u0438\u043c \u043e\u0440\u0434\u0435\u043d\u043e\u043c \u0422\u0430\u0434\u0436\u0438\u043a\u0438\u0441\u0442\u0430\u043d\u0430|trans-title=Xi Jinping awarded the highest order of Tajikistan|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190905163817/https://news.ru/world/si-czinpin-nagrazhdyon-vysshim-ordenom-tadzhikistana/|archive-date=5 September 2019|access-date=5 September 2019}}</ref>\n\n; Key to the City\n* {{flagdeco|US}}{{flagicon|Iowa}} [[Muscatine, Iowa]], U.S. (26 April 1985)<ref name=\"National Public Radio2\">{{cite news|url=https://www.npr.org/2012/02/14/146888717/iowa-a-top-destination-for-chinas-vice-president/|title=A Familiar Face Back in Iowa: China's Vice President|last=|first=|date=14 February 2012|newspaper=[[NPR]]|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190714065854/https://www.npr.org/2012/02/14/146888717/iowa-a-top-destination-for-chinas-vice-president|archive-date=14 July 2019|access-date=7 September 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/magazine-17022158|title=The early adventures of Xi Jinping|last=Dailey|first=Kate|date=15 February 2012|newspaper=[[BBC News]]|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190331084433/https://www.bbc.com/news/magazine-17022158|archive-date=31 March 2019|access-date=7 September 2019}}</ref>\n* {{flagdeco|US}}{{flagdeco|Iowa}} [[Muscatine, Iowa]], U.S. (14 February 2012)<ref name=\"National Public Radio2\" />\n* {{flagdeco|JAM}} [[Montego Bay]], Jamaica (13 February 2009)<ref>{{cite news|url=http://jis.gov.jm/chinese-vp-receives-key-to-the-city-of-montego-bay/|title=Chinese VP Receives Key to the City of Montego Bay|last=|first=|date=15 February 2009|newspaper=Jamaica Information Service|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190714065907/https://jis.gov.jm/chinese-vp-receives-key-to-the-city-of-montego-bay/|archive-date=14 July 2019|access-date=7 September 2019}}</ref>\n* {{flagdeco|CRI}}{{flagu|San Jos\u00e9, Costa Rica}} (3 June 2013)<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite news|url=http://english.cctv.com/2016/04/06/ARTIOaYH7rGq8JoM8ZFDN64C160406.shtml|title=How many Keys to City has Xi Jinping received?|last=Chen|first=Yue|date=6 April 2016|newspaper=[[China Central Television]]|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190507174548/http://english.cctv.com/2016/04/06/ARTIOaYH7rGq8JoM8ZFDN64C160406.shtml|archive-date=7 May 2019|access-date=5 September 2019}}</ref>\n* {{flagdeco|MEX}}{{flagu|Mexico City}}, Mexico (5 June 2013)<ref name=\":0\" />\n* {{flagdeco|ARG}}{{flagu|Buenos Aires}}, Argentina (19 July 2014)<ref name=\":0\" />\n*{{flagdeco|CZE}}{{flagu|Prague}}, Czech Republic (29 March 2016)<ref name=\":0\" />\n* {{flagdeco|ESP}}{{flagicon|City of Madrid}} [[Madrid]], Spain (28 November 2018)<ref>{{cite news|url=https://news.cgtn.com/news/3d3d514d7949544f30457a6333566d54/index.html|title=President Xi receives Golden Key of Madrid, vows to open up doors of communication further|date=28 November 2018|newspaper=[[CGTN]]|accessdate=13 May 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190513085728/https://news.cgtn.com/news/3d3d514d7949544f30457a6333566d54/index.html|archive-date=13 May 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n== Notes ==\n{{NoteFoot}}\n{{notelist}}\n\n== References ==\n=== Citations ===\n{{Reflist}}\n\n=== Works cited ===\n{{refbegin|40em}}\n* {{Cite book|title=China's Management Revolution: Spirit, Land, Energy|last=Bou\u00e9e|first=Charles-Edouard|publisher=[[Palgrave Macmillan]]|year=2010|isbn=978-0-230-2854