ne/blogs/evanosnos/2012/02/chinas-valentines-day-in-washington.html \"China's Valentine's Day in Washington\"], ''The New Yorker'', 14 February 2012. Review of comment accompanying Xi's visit.\n* [[Evan Osnos|Osnos, Evan]], [https://www.newyorker.com/magazine/2015/04/06/born-red \"Born Red: How Xi Jinping, an unremarkable provincial administrator, became China's most authoritarian leader since Mao\"]''The New Yorker'', 30 March 30, 2015. Describes Xi Jinping's life.\n* [https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b01nnw8l Xi Jinping 2012 profile] on [[BBC Radio Four]]\n{{-}}{{Xi Jinping}}{{Navboxes|title=Offices and distinctions of Xi Jinping|list1={{s-start}}\n{{s-off|prc}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[He Guoqiang]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[Politics of Fujian|Governor of Fujian Province]]|years=1999\u20132002}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[Lu Zhangong]]}}\n{{s-break}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[Chai Songyue]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[Politics of Zhejiang|Governor of Zhejiang Province]]|years=2002\u20132003}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[L\u00fc Zushan]]}}\n{{s-break}}\n{{s-bef|before=Li Zemin}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[Politics of Zhejiang|Chairman of the People's Congress Standing Committee of Zhejiang]]|years=2003\u20132007}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[Yu Guoxing]]}}\n{{s-break}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[Zeng Qinghong]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[Vice President of the People's Republic of China]]|years=2008\u20132013}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[Li Yuanchao]]}}\n{{s-break}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[Xu Caihou]]<br />[[Guo Boxiong]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[Central Military Commission (China)|Vice Chairman of the Central Military Commission]]|years=2010\u20132013}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[Fan Changlong]]<br />[[Xu Qiliang]]}}\n{{s-break}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[Hu Jintao]]|rows=2}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[President of the People's Republic of China]]|years=2013\u2013present}}\n{{s-inc|rows=2}}\n{{s-break}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[Chairman of the Central Military Commission]]|years=2013\u2013present}}\n{{s-break}}\n{{s-ppo|{{cpc}}}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[Zhang Dejiang]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[Party chief of the Communis