13|publisher=Australian Football League Umpires Association}}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size: 95%;\"\n|+ 2013 AFL Grand Final umpires\n! Position !! Umpire 1 !! Umpire 2 !! Umpire 3 !! Umpire 4 !! rowspan=\"4\" |  !! Emergency\n|-\n| {{rh}} | [[Umpire (Australian rules football)|Field]]:\n| 8 [[Brett Rosebury]] (6)\n| 15 [[Mathew Nicholls]] (1)\n| 21 [[Simon Meredith (umpire)|Simon Meredith]] (2)\n| \n| 9 [[Matt Stevic]]\n|-\n| style=\"background:#efefef;\"| '''[[Umpire (Australian rules football)|Boundary]]:\n| Nathan Doig (2)\n| Robert Haala (2)\n| Michael Marantelli (1)\n| Michael Saunders (1)\n| Matthew Tomkins\n|-\n| style=\"background:#efefef;\"| '''[[Umpire (Australian rules football)|Goal]]:\n| Luke Walker (5)\n| Adam Wojcik (1)\n|\n| \n| Chris Appleton\n|}\n''Numbers in brackets represent the number of grand finals umpired; this number includes 2013 and does not include times selected as an emergency umpire.''\n\n==Scorecard==\n\n{{AFLGameDetailed\n|title = Grand Final\n|date = Saturday, 28 September (2:30&nbsp;pm)\n|home team = {{AFL Haw}}\n|home Q1 = 2.3 (15)\n|home Q2 = 5.5 (35)\n|home Q3 = 8.8 (56)\n|home final = 11.11 (77)\n|home goals= [[Jack Gunston|Gunston]] 4<br/> [[Jarryd Roughead|Roughead]] 2<br/> [[Lance Franklin|Franklin]], [[Cyril Rioli|Rioli]], [[Isaac Smith (footballer)|Smith]], [[Luke Breust|Breust]], [[Bradley Hill (footballer)|Hill]] 1\n|home best = &nbsp; [[Brian Lake|Lake]], [[Jack Gunston|Gunston]], [[Jordan Lewis|Lewis]], [[Cyril Rioli|Rioli]], [[Luke Hodge|Hodge]], [[Grant Birchall|Birchall]]\n|home injuries = &nbsp; Nil\n|home reports = [[Brian Lake|Lake]] - Striking; [[Cyril Rioli|Rioli]] - Rough conduct\n|winner = H\n|away team = {{AFL Fre}}\n|away Q1 = 0.3 (3)\n|away Q2 = 1.6 (12)\n|away Q3 = 6.10 (46)\n|away final = 8.14 (62)\n|away goals= 3 [[Matthew Pavlich|Pavlich]]<br/>2 [[Michael Walters|Walters]]<br/>1 [[Tendai Mzungu|Mzungu]], [[Chris Mayne|Mayne]], [[Danyle Pearce|Pearce]]\n|away best= &nbsp; [[David Mundy|Mundy]], [[Nathan Fyfe|Fyfe]], [[Ryan Crowley|Crowley]], [[Michael Johnson (footballer born 1988)|Johnson]], [[Michael Barlow|Barlow]]\n|away injuries = &nbsp; Nil\n|away reports = [[Nick Suban|Suban]] - Misconduct\n|venue =  <abbr title=\"15\u00b0 A few showers clearing. Windy.\">[[File:Soare cu nori.png|16px]]</abbr> [[Melbourne Cricket Ground|MCG]]\n|crowd = 100,007\n|report = [http://www.afl.com.au/match-centre/2013/27/haw-v-fre Report]\n|umpires = [[Brett Rosebury]], [[Mathew Nicholls]], [[Simon Meredith (umpire)|Simon Meredith]]\n|BOG award = [[Norm Smith Medal]]\n|BOG winner = [[Brian Lake]]\n|broadcast = [[Seven Network]]\n|anthem = [[Tina Arena]]\n}}\n\n==Tribunal==\nThe following Monday, the [[AFL Tribunal|Match Review Panel]] adjudicated on two offences incurred by Hawthorn's [[Brian Lake]] and [[Cyril Rioli]], both of which carried the double points loading of due to being incurred during a grand final.  The third offence of misconduct against Fremantle's [[Nick Suban]] was referred directly to the Tribunal for assessment, which determined the incident was improper but not grievous. Suban pleaded guilty to the incident and apologized for what he felt to be an accident.\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|- style=\"background:#efefef;\"\n! Player\n! Charge\n! Penalty\n|-\n|[[Nick Suban]], [[Fremantle Football Club|Fremantle]]\n|Unreasonable and unnecessary contact to the face of [[Sam Mitchell (footballer)|Sam Mitchell]], [[Hawthorn Football Club|Hawthorn]], in the 1st Quarter.<ref name=\"gf-reports\">{{cite web|url=http://www.afl.com.au/news/2013-09-30/hawk-heroes-handed-bans|title=Hawk heroes handed bans|date=30 September 2013|author=David Schout|publisher=Australian Football League}}</ref>\n|Referred to the Tribunal. Suban pleaded guilty; suspended one match.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.abc.net.au/news/2013-10-01/suban-to-miss-one-afl-game/4992272?section=sport|title=Fremantle's Nick Suban to miss one AFL game after grand final gouge on Hawthorn's Sam Mitchell|date=1 October 2013}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[Cyril Rioli]], [[Hawthorn Football Club|Hawthorn]]\n|Rough conduct (chicken-wing tackle) against [[Michael Barlow]], [[Fremantle Football Club|Fremantle]], in the 3rd Quarter.<ref name=\"gf-reports\" />\n|Pled guilty; suspended one match.<ref name=\"gf-pleas\">{{cite web|url=http://www.afl.com.au/news/2013-10-02/lake-rioli-to-miss-2014-start|title=Lake, Rioli to miss start of next season|date=2 October 2013|author=Mark Macgugan|publisher=Australian Football League}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[Brian Lake]], [[Hawthorn Football Club|Hawthorn]]\n|Striking [[Michael Walters]], [[Fremantle Football Club|Fremantle]], in the 3rd Quarter.<ref name=\"gf-reports\" />\n|Pled guilty; suspended three matches.<ref name=\"gf-pleas\" />\n|}\n\n==See also==\n* [[2013 NAB Cup]]\n* [[2013 AFL season]]\n* [[2013 AFL finals series]]\n\n==References==\n{{Commons category}}\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{2013 Hawthorn premiership players}}\n{{Hawthorn Football Club}}\n{{Fremantle Football Club}}\n{{2013 AFL season}}\n{{Australian Football League}}\n\n[[Category:VFL/AFL Grand Finals]]\n[[Category:2013 Australian Football League season|Grand Final]]\n[[Category:Hawthorn Football Club]]\n[[Category:Fremantle Football Club]]\n", "name_user": "John of Reading", "label": "safe", "comment": "Typo fixing, replaced: teams history \u2192 team's history, ]]\u2019s \u2192 ]]'s", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2013_AFL_Grand_Final"}
